    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning (09:15:00) in the Grand Atrium of The Athenaeum of Whispers\u2014you make your way across the marble floor, your footsteps muted against the ancient stones. The elderly half-elf looks up as you approach, her pale eyes reflecting decades of scholarly patience.\n\n\"I couldn't help noticing,\" you say quietly, inclining your head toward the upper gallery, \"that locked iron door. The Forbidden Depository, is it? I've never seen it opened in all my visits.\"\n\nCaelindis (Lvl 3) pauses in her work, her weathered hands stilling over the scrolls. A faint smile crosses her lined face\u2014amused, perhaps, but also wary.\n\n\"The Forgotten Depository,\" she corrects gently. \"And some knowledge is best left... forgotten.\" She studies you for a moment, reading whatever motives lie behind your curiosity. \"The texts within date from before the Sundering. Some say they contain truths too dangerous for mortal minds. Others claim they're merely old tax records.\" Her eyebrows rise. \"Which would you believe?\"\n\nShe straightens, folding her hands before her. \"Access requires authorization from the Council of Scrolls. They've grown... cautious in recent years. Many requests come, few are granted.\" Her gaze flickers briefly toward the cloaked figure in the corner, then back to you. \"Tell me, scholar\u2014what is it you truly seek?\"",
      "actor": "gemini",
